               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400914-name-589" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400914-name-589" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400914-name-589" type="surname" value="ALDRIDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400914-name-589" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES ALDRIDGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Northumberland-street, Strand, and am a jeweller—the prisoner was my apprentice. On Sunday, the 13th of Sep<lb></lb>tember, somebody came to my house, and showed me a gold cutting—I cannot swear to the gold, but I verily believe it to be mine—I have gone over my stock, and missed about six pennyweights of gold—it was kept in a tin can—the prisoner and all the other men in the shop had access to it.</p>
